bums before taking up the ministry in 1983. He began recording again in 1997, and over the next twenty-five years he released two Christian and five secular albums.In this biography of Rock & Roll Hall of Famer Richie Furay, Thomas Kitts provides an intimate look at Furay’s life and music. Kitts chronicles the musician’s upbringing, his musical career, and his Christianity, drawing on interviews with Furay and others close to him. In documenting Furay’s extraordinary talent as a songwriter, vocalist, and guitarist, Kitts argues that although he never attained the level of stardom of many of his bandmates, Furay is a pivotal figure in American popular music.Fans of Buffalo Springfield, Poco, and country-rock music will enjoy this quintessentially American story of a young man on a quest to fulfill his rock-and-roll dreams.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLyricistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aRock musicianszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh  aAu Go-Go singers.  aBuffalo Springfield.  aChristian country.  aChristian music.  aChristian rock.  aLaurel Canyon.  aPoco.  aRichie Furay.  aRock and Roll Hall of Fame.  aSouther-Hillman-Furay.  aThe Richie Furay Band.  acountry rock.  aevangelical.  afolk rock.  aneglected singer-songwriters.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079775640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271096322?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271096322423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271096322/original  a978-3-11-079775-6  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles